<h2 class="subhead">Sexual orientation</h2><div style="clear:both;">Homophobic crime is a hate crime. <br />
<br />
Crimes which are mainly or partly 
motivated by animosity towards 
lesbians, gay men or bisexuals, and 
may include:<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><ul><li>Verbal abuse and name calling. </li>
<li>Having your property defaced with anti-
lesbian or anti-gay slogans. </li>
<li>Being robbed in the street or burgled 
at home. </li>
<li>Being attacked outside gay bars or 
other venues. </li>
<li>Rape or sexual assault.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="clear:both;">Merseyside Police work with the 
Lesbian, Gay and Bisexual (LGB) 
communities in order to make sure 
their concerns about homophobic crime 
are met.<br />
<br />
For further information on the 
Merseyside Police LGB policy and how 
to report a homophobic crime, visit 
the Merseyside Police website (see below).<br />
<br />
</div>
